d to thinking and feeling. Avidly Reads is an exciting new series featuring books that are part memoir, part cultural criticism, each bringing to life the author’s emotional relationship to a cultural artifact or experience. Avidly Reads invites us to explore the surprising pleasures and obstacles of everyday life.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Mrz 2024) 7aBIOGRAPHY & AUTOBIOGRAPHY / Literary.2bisacsh  aA Body, Undone.  aA Patch of Blue.  aBataille.  aBeloved.  aCapturing the Friedmans.  aDeleuze.  aEvangelical.  aFire.  aGod.  aGuattari.  aHoop Dreams.  aLolita.  aMoonlight.  aOrlando.  aTa-Nehisi Coates.  aTaussig.  aThe Picture of Dorian Gray.  aVillette.  aableism.  abarebacking.  abeing outed.  abodily orifice.  abullying.  achildhood.  adefacement.  adesire.  adildo.  aface.  afaces.  agay.  agift books.  agroup kissing.  agroup think.  ahomosexuality.  ainterpretation.  ainterracial kiss.  akissing.  alesbian.  amarriage.  amemoir.  anegation.  anon-binary gender.  apain.  apolice.  aprofessor.  apurity.  aqueer child.  aqueer sexuality.  arace.  aracism.  areading.  asex with ideas.  aslavery.  asurface reading.  asurface/depth.  ateenage.  atrans.  atransgender.  awoman.  awords getting into us.40uhttps://doi.org/10.18574/nyu/9781479814206.001.000140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781479814206423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781479814206/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LT  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles